  "_class_aliases_doc": "Class-scoped aliases.  Apply ONLY when the lookup is qualified with an element type.  Use for aliases whose name collides with a canonical attribute on a different element class — e.g. `discharge` is the canonical attribute of `flow` (Flow element), but a legacy alias of `target` *within flow_right*.  Promoting that to the global `aliases[]` would break Flow parsing; the class scope confines the rewrite to `flow_right` lookups only.  The JSON-input canonicalize step is class-blind and ignores this section; only the AMPL resolver consults it (via `canonical_for(class, alias)`).",
